article.headline: Winthrop 72, High Point 55
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Torrell Martin scored 21 points Tuesday as Winthrop used a second-half spurt to beat High Point 72-55 in the Big South Conference. Winthrop (18-5, 9-1) led 34-33 at halftime, then shot 54 percent from the field and 58.3 percent from the line to outrun High Point (10-13, 5-5). Winthrop got 16 points and 11 rebounds from James Shuler and 12 points from Otis Daniels to win their ninth-straight game. Mark Wilson led the Panthers with 15 points. High Point said before the game that senior forward Danny Gathings has been suspended indefinitely for a violation of team rules. Gathings, from Winston-Salem, was averaging 13.6 points and 6.8 rebounds per game while shooting 51 percent from the floor this season. Gathings was last season's Big South player of the year and the most valuable player of the conference tournament.
